HEADWORD: Boation
<hw>Bo*a"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>boatus</ets>, fr. <ets>boare</ets> to roar.]</ety> <def>A crying
out; a roaring; a bellowing; reverberation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The guns were heard . . . about a hundred Italian miles, in long
<qex>boations</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Derham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boatman</ent>⟦br⟧
